One of the best things about this theme is how easy it is to customize. Let's walk through the main ways you can make it your own.

## Changing the Primary Color

The entire color scheme is built around CSS custom properties. Open `src/lib/styles/global.css` and find these variables:

```css
:root {
  --primary-hue: 260;
  --primary-saturation: 60%;
}
```

Change the `--primary-hue` value (0-360) to shift the entire color palette:

| Hue | Color |
|-----|-------|
| 0   | Red   |
| 60  | Yellow |
| 120 | Green |
| 180 | Cyan  |
| 240 | Blue  |
| 300 | Magenta |

## Typography

The theme uses Inter for body text and JetBrains Mono for code. You can swap these out by modifying the font imports in `src/app.html` and updating the CSS variables:

```css
:root {
  --font-sans: 'Your Font', sans-serif;
  --font-mono: 'Your Mono Font', monospace;
}
```

## Site Configuration

Edit `src/lib/config.ts` to update:

- Site title and description
- Author name
- Social links
- Navigation menu items

> **Tip:** The social links in the footer automatically show/hide based on whether you've provided URLs for each platform.

## Adding Your Own Styles

Want to add custom styles? You can either:

1. Modify `src/lib/styles/global.css` directly
2. Create a new CSS file and import it in your layout

## Dark Mode

The theme automatically supports system preference for dark mode, but users can also toggle it manually. The preference is saved to localStorage.

---

That's the basics! Have fun customizing your new blog.
